description.narrative: (Cambodia): The Quality Health Services (QHS) project will improve quality of services in public-sector clinics and hospitals, to improve maternal, neonatal and child healthcare in nine focus provinces. With FY 2017 funds, the QHS project will continue to provide on-site coaching to health providers on newborn care and basic and emergency obstetric care (including prevention and treatment of postpartum hemorrhage, pre-eclampsia and eclampsia). QHS will improve the skills of healthcare providers to screen and treat severe acute malnutrition according to national standards. QHS will also train healthcare providers to identify and treat nutrition-related issues and pediatric TB and improve infection control in public-sector facilities. The project will reach up to 600 facilities and serve nearly six million people. In FY 2017, QHS will begin transitioning its intervention to the host government.
